<p>i'm trying to get some ideas to get the values generated by the IBAction into one class.</p>  <p>In facts: There is an IBAction inside the Class named <strong>TabBarController</strong> (type UiTabBarController, embedded with Navigation Controller and generated via StoryBoard) where is possible to set the values of the segment. </p>  <p>The problem is trying to get these values stored in the variable <strong>VideoLIS</strong> from another Class that is switched by <strong>TabBarController</strong>. It's Boolean becuase it will be used as "switch" to get Video or Text that i have to launch.</p>  <p>in TabBarController.h</p>  <pre><code>#import &lt;UIKit/UIKit.h&gt;    @interface TabBarController: UITabBarController  {      UISegmentedControl *segmentControl;      @public      BOOL *videoLIS;   }    @property (readwrite) BOOL *videoLIS;   @property (nonatomic, retain) IBOutlet UISegmentedControl *segmentControl;   @property (nonatomic) BOOL *checkSegmentedControlState;    -(IBAction) segmentedControlChanged;   -(BOOL) statoLIS;   -(BOOL) checkSegmentedControlState;  @end </code></pre>  <p>in TabBarController.m</p>  <pre><code> #import "TabBarController.h"   @implementation TabBarController   @synthesize segmentControl;  @synthesize videoLIS;  @synthesize checkSegmentedControlState;   - (void)viewDidLoad {      [super viewDidLoad];      videoLIS=TRUE;   }   -IBAction **segmentedControlChanged**{         switch (segmentControl.selectedSegmentIndex) {             case 0:                videoLIS=TRUE;                NSLog(**videoLIS** ? @"LIS" : @"Testo");                break;             case 1:                NSLog(@"TEXT Selected");                videoLIS=FALSE;                NSLog(**videoLIS** ? @"LIS" : @"Testo");                break;             default:              break;             }  } </code></pre>  <p>How to get the Value of videoLIS from another class (UIViewController)?</p>  <p>I was considering to use the NSNotification ... or do you have other solutions? Thanks a lot for your help.</p>  <p>EDIT: I tried another solution. I dropped this way and moved the UISegmentControl into every ViewControllers, so I have the result inside the Class without worrying about this.So result come now.</p>  <p>Thanks a lot for your hints.</p>